    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "(Subverting issue template as it doesn't seem to apply)\r\n\r\nCurrently, all commands defined via the RPC interface have to use f-args as the input method for the arguments, see https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/fcc9d999670c6fb29ac01e9c8d0a7e787ccfabea/runtime/autoload/remote/define.vim#L58\r\n\r\nIt could be useful to use the others, e.g. `<args>`, `<q-args>` etc.\r\n\r\nIt could be made part of the api, and then exposed by the RPC clients for command definition.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
